<subSubSection pageId="18" pageNumber="249" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph blockId="18.[151,1437,504,819]" pageId="18" pageNumber="249">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,279,504,530]" pageId="18" pageNumber="249">Type data:</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Friese, H." box="[287,437,504,530]" pageId="18" pageNumber="249" pagination="39 - 48" refId="ref21677" refString="Friese, H. (1899) Neue arten der Bienengattungen Epicharis Klug und Centris Fabr. Termeszetrajzi Fuzetek, 23, 39 - 48." type="journal article" year="1899">Friese (1899)</bibRefCitation>
proposed this species based on specimens of both sexes collected in 
<collectingCountry box="[1216,1315,505,531]" name="Uruguay" pageId="18" pageNumber="249">Uruguay</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1325,1436,504,530]" name="Argentina" pageId="18" pageNumber="249">Argentina</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[198,270,540,566]" name="Brazil" pageId="18" pageNumber="249">Brazil</collectingCountry>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Zanella, F. C. V." box="[279,444,540,566]" pageId="18" pageNumber="249" pagination="435 - 488" refId="ref24081" refString="Zanella, F. C. V. (2002) Sistematica, filogenia e distribuicao geografica das especies sul-americanas de Centris (Paracentris) Cameron, 1903 e de Centris (Penthemisia) Moure, 1950, incluindo uma analise filogenetica do grupo Centris, sensu Ayala, 1998 (Hymenoptera: Apoidea: Centridini). Revista Brasileira de Entomologia, 46 (4), 435 - 488. https: // doi. org / 10.1590 / s 0085 - 56262002000400001" type="journal article" year="2002">Zanella (2002)</bibRefCitation>
designated a specimen from Montevideo housed at 
<collectionCode box="[1019,1080,541,567]" country="Germany" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/8syf-d21i" name="Museum für Naturkunde Berlin (Zoological Collections)" pageId="18" pageNumber="249" type="Museum">ZMB</collectionCode>
as the 
<typeStatus box="[1155,1261,540,566]" pageId="18" pageNumber="249">lectotype</typeStatus>
. This exemplar, as well as the 
<typeStatus box="[312,415,576,602]" pageId="18" pageNumber="249">lectotype</typeStatus>
and 
<typeStatus box="[471,622,576,602]" pageId="18" pageNumber="249">paralectotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Friese" authorityYear="1899" box="[660,872,576,603]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="249" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="labrosa" subSpecies="simplex">
<emphasis box="[660,679,576,602]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="249">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[694,872,576,602]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="249">labrosa simplex</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, was collected by Friedrich Sellow (see comment on that species) and it has the following data label: [green label] Montevid. Sello. [printed]\ 1575 [handwritten]\ 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Friese" authorityYear="1899" box="[151,326,648,674]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="249" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tricolor">
<emphasis box="[151,326,648,674]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="249">Centris tricolor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<specimenCount box="[332,353,649,675]" pageId="18" pageNumber="249" type="female">♀</specimenCount>
[handwritten] det. Friese 1898 [printed]\ Zool. Mus. Berlin [printed with blue ink]\ [orange label with black rim] Type [printed]\ [pink label] 
<typeStatus box="[635,795,684,710]" pageId="18" pageNumber="249">LECTOTYPE</typeStatus>
<taxonomicName authority=", Friese F. Zanella, 1998" authorityName=", Friese F. Zanella" authorityYear="1998" box="[800,1240,684,711]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="249" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tricolor">
<emphasis box="[800,974,684,710]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="249">Centris tricolor</emphasis>
, Friese F. Zanella, 1998
</taxonomicName>
[printed] (
<collectionCode box="[1358,1424,684,710]" country="Germany" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/8syf-d21i" name="Museum für Naturkunde Berlin (Zoological Collections)" pageId="18" pageNumber="249" type="Museum">ZMB</collectionCode>
). The current condition and depository of the 
<typeStatus box="[645,807,720,746]" pageId="18" pageNumber="249">paralectotypes</typeStatus>
are unknown.
</paragraph>
